This species was described based on a couple of female and male specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF820873CAA23431FFB62DE12AE8F" box="[1282,1394,1168,1194]" country="Peru" name="Arequipa" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Arequipa</collectingRegion>
, southern 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873CAA234736FB45DA05AEF4" box="[299,357,1207,1233]" name="Peru" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Both specimens were collected by Edmundo Escomel (
<date id="FFD51002873CAA234219FB44DFEEAEF4" box="[1028,1166,1206,1233]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" value="1880" valueMax="1959">1880–1959</date>
), a Peruvian doctor who dedicated his free time as a meticulous observer of the flora, fauna and the natural environment (Velarde 2006). The male 
<typeStatus id="54D08860873CAA2347E7FAF1D901AF38" box="[506,609,1283,1309]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13502A47873CAA23446EFAF1D9ABAF38" box="[627,715,1283,1309]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="39.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="Fig. 29. Centris escomeli Cockerell, 1926, holotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534193). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3723006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3723006/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) and the female 
<typeStatus id="54D08860873CAA234585FAF6D89DAF3B" box="[920,1021,1284,1310]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">paratype</typeStatus>
are housed at the 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07873CAA2342C2FAF6DE5DAF3B" box="[1247,1341,1284,1310]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54D08860873CAA2346A0FADBDA44AF66" box="[189,292,1321,1347]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">holotype</typeStatus>
has the following data label: 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF820873CAA23449AFADBD994AF66" box="[647,756,1321,1347]" country="Peru" name="Arequipa" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Arequipa</collectingRegion>
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873CAA2344E0FAD8D853AF61" box="[765,819,1322,1348]" name="Peru" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Peru</collectingCountry>
(Escomel) [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41873CAA234273FAD8DE16AF61" authority="Ckll." authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1926" box="[1134,1398,1321,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="escomeli">
